{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}} {{Infobox website |name = OpenBSD Journal |logo = OpenBSD Journal Logo.jpg |logocaption = |screenshot = |collapsible = |collapsetext = |caption = |url = {{official URL}} |slogan = |commercial = No |type = [[Online newspaper]] |registration = Optional |language = English |num_users = |content_license = [[All rights reserved]] |owner = Paul de Weerd |author = Daniel Hartmeier |launch_date = {{Start date and age|2004|4|9|df=yes}} |alexa = {{IncreaseNegative}} 651798 {{as of|2014|7|19|lc=yes}}<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/undeadly.org |title = Undeadly.org Site Info |work = [[Alexa Internet]] |accessdate = 19 July 2014 }}</ref> |revenue = |current_status = Online |footnotes = }}
The '''OpenBSD Journal''' is an [[online newspaper]] dedicated to coverage of [[OpenBSD]] software and related events.
== History == The OpenBSD Journal was founded in 2000 and operated until 1 April 2004 at {{URL|deadly.org}}. On 1 April 2004 the editors James Phillips and Jose Nazario announced that the site ceased its operation.<ref name="deadly-announce" /> Daniel Hartmeier backed up the contents of the journal in order to preserve them.<ref name="onlamp-reborn" /> Further investigation to the articles' structure lead to creation of [[Common Gateway Interface|CGI]]-based engine that would enable access to the deadly.org's content on a backup server. Consequently, the functionality of adding new articles was implemented and the previous editors allowed to re-publish articles. The OpenBSD Journal was therefore reintroduced at {{URL|undeadly.org}} on 9 April 2004.<ref name="undeadly-about" />
== The role in OpenBSD community == The OpenBSD Journal is widely recognized as a [[WP:RS|reliable source]] of OpenBSD-related information.<ref name="onlamp-reborn" /><ref name="the-book-of-pf" /><ref name="absolute-openbsd" /> It is a primary reporter for such events as [[Hackathon]]s. The site also hosts the OpenBSD developers' blogs.
== Editors == The current editors of OpenBSD Journal are:<ref name="undeadly-about" /> *Janne Johansson *Peter Hessler *Peter N. M. Hansteen *tj *grey *Nayden Markatchev *Ross Richardson
